/span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">I may be <span class=\"cl\">stating the obvious</span> but without more money the project cannot survive.</span></li></ul>      </li><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" id=\"obvious_unbox_5\" unbox=\"wordorigin\"><span class=\"box_title\">Word Origin</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">late 16th cent. (in the sense ‘frequently encountered’): from Latin <span class=\"ei\">obvius</span> (from the phrase <span class=\"ei\">ob viam</span> ‘in the way’) + <span class=\"eb\">-ous</span>.</span></span></span></div></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/obvious\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">obvious</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/academic/obvious\" title=\" definition in Academic English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">obvious</span></a> in the Oxford Learner's Dictionary of Academic English</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/obvious\">obvious</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["obverse noun","obviate verb","obvious adjective","obviously adverb","obviousness noun"]},[]]